WEBVTT

00:04.338 --> 00:06.440
[ Man ]
One, two. One, two, three!

00:31.964 --> 00:34.468
So I gave the cookies
you made to Fawn and the kids,

00:34.567 --> 00:36.704
and they couldn't believe it!

00:36.804 --> 00:39.972
They were delicious!
But I digress.

00:40.073 --> 00:44.378
Tremble, puny earthlings!
One day my race will
destroy you all.

00:44.478 --> 00:47.280
[ Doorbell Ringing,
Footsteps Departing ]

00:47.381 --> 00:49.417
Could one of you guys
get that?

00:53.820 --> 00:56.323
[ Baby Cooing ]
[ Gasping ]

00:56.423 --> 00:58.625
It's a doorbell baby!

00:58.725 --> 01:02.630
Hello, little guy. You know,
I was abandoned as a baby too.

01:02.729 --> 01:05.132
So--
Garbage, huh?
I'll take care of it.

01:05.233 --> 01:07.168
[ Blow Landing,
Bender Grunting ]
Bender, stop!

01:07.268 --> 01:10.337
- It's a baby!
- A baby what? Ow!

01:12.406 --> 01:16.075
Oh, it's just a card!
From the orphanarium
I grew up in.

01:16.176 --> 01:20.581
[ Recorded Baby Voice ]
Oh! Leela, you're invited
to a reunion...

01:20.680 --> 01:24.418
at Cookieville Minimum-Security
Orphanarium.

01:24.518 --> 01:27.019
[ Woman's Recorded Voice ]
Please stand clear of
self-destructing basket.

01:27.120 --> 01:31.658
- [ Leela Whimpering ]
- A reunion at your old
orphanarium, eh?

01:31.759 --> 01:34.495
You gonna go?
No way, JosÃ©bot.

01:34.594 --> 01:36.764
I never want to see
those other orphans again.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.599
Not after the way
they used to pick on me.

01:39.700 --> 01:42.436
[ Children Chanting ]
One Eye, One Eye, One Eye!

01:42.536 --> 01:44.938
Nice depth perception,
One Eye!

01:45.037 --> 01:46.973
[ Laughing ]

01:47.073 --> 01:49.777
How can you
make fun of me, Kirk?
You're blind!

01:49.877 --> 01:53.013
My eyes may not work,
but at least I got two of them.

01:53.112 --> 01:55.848
[ Laughing ]

01:55.948 --> 01:58.152
[ Sighs ]
Oh.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.022
Aw, that's terrible, Leela.

02:02.121 --> 02:04.825
But imagine the look
on their faces when you
show up with two friends...

02:04.924 --> 02:07.227
who eat all the hors d'oeuvres.
Well.

02:07.328 --> 02:10.330
I wouldn't mind
rubbing my success in
a few choice faces.

02:10.431 --> 02:12.400
Set a course
for adventure!

02:14.033 --> 02:16.036
[ Banging,
Whirring ]

02:16.135 --> 02:18.671
[ Hooting ]

02:18.771 --> 02:20.674
Ew!
[ Bender ]
What a dump!

02:20.774 --> 02:24.044
[ Sighing ] Oh!
Just like old times.

02:24.144 --> 02:28.581
Gosh.
The bars on the windows seemed
so much thicker back then.

02:30.016 --> 02:32.019
[ Clears Throat ]
Mr. Vogel?

02:32.118 --> 02:34.222
- Remember me?
- Leela!

02:34.322 --> 02:36.223
You're worthless, and no one
will ever love you!

02:36.324 --> 02:40.427
[ Laughing ]
You used to say that
all the time.

02:40.527 --> 02:42.663
Ah! Those were
happier days.

02:42.763 --> 02:44.997
** [ Band ]

02:49.736 --> 02:53.841
Mm. The "gristle in a blanket"
isn't half-bad.
[ Swallowing ]

02:53.941 --> 02:57.411
And try one of these popsicle
sticks. They've absorbed
quite a bit of flavor.

02:57.510 --> 03:00.681
Hey, look. It's our
old group picture.

03:01.681 --> 03:04.084
I don't see you
anywhere.

03:04.183 --> 03:06.387
That's me,
over in "Cootie-town."

03:06.486 --> 03:09.188
Whoo! Get a load of
this average-looking guy.

03:09.289 --> 03:12.592
That's Adlai Atkins.
I used to have kind of
a crush on him.

03:14.093 --> 03:15.728
[ Children ]
One Eye, One Eye!

03:15.829 --> 03:21.634
Stupid as a French guy!
One Eye, One Eye,
One Eye, One Eye--

03:21.735 --> 03:25.473
[ All Continue Chanting ]

03:25.573 --> 03:27.807
[ Sighs Deeply ]

03:29.209 --> 03:32.479
Well, it's time to say
hello to the old gang.

03:32.579 --> 03:36.650
[ Gulping ]

03:40.920 --> 03:43.824
So? What you been
up to since you
left the orphanarium?

03:43.924 --> 03:47.295
Oh, livin' in a box,
fightin' the shakes. You?

03:47.395 --> 03:50.062
Sellin' kidneys, teeth.
Whatever falls out of me.

03:50.163 --> 03:54.468
And what am I up to,
you ask? Why, I'm a very
successful space captain.

03:54.567 --> 03:56.469
Oh!
Wow!

03:56.569 --> 03:59.105
How nice for you,
Leela.
That's so good...

03:59.206 --> 04:01.140
for a person
with one eye.

04:01.241 --> 04:04.412
Hey! You can't feel
sorry for me.

04:04.512 --> 04:07.480
I'm a space captain, and
you're a bunch of losers.

04:07.580 --> 04:12.118
Uh, right. Right.
We're the losers.
[ Coughs ]

04:12.218 --> 04:16.790
Well, if it isn't
old One Eye.
[ Laughing ]

04:16.889 --> 04:20.293
Oh, yeah? Well,
shut up, Cane Boy!

04:20.394 --> 04:22.329
He can't hear ya.
He's deaf now.

04:22.430 --> 04:25.533
Leave Leela alone.
She's leading
a perfectly normal life.

04:25.632 --> 04:29.269
She's not gussied up,
duded out, getting down,
or where it's at.

04:29.370 --> 04:31.838
Now, run along.

04:33.473 --> 04:37.511
Thanks, Adlai. I guess
you never really outgrow
being an eyeball--

04:37.610 --> 04:41.213
- Oddball.
- Nonsense, you're
a space captain.

04:41.314 --> 04:44.050
- That's a fine,
conventional profession.
- Well, you know.

04:44.151 --> 04:46.620
It's just for
a package delivery service.

04:46.720 --> 04:50.156
Ah-ah! A package is just
a box until it's delivered.

04:50.257 --> 04:52.560
Huh! I'd never thought
of it that way.

04:52.659 --> 04:54.627
So what do you do
these days?

04:54.728 --> 04:58.331
- Oh, I'm a doctor.
- A tall doctor, you say.

04:58.432 --> 05:01.134
[ Gulping ]

05:02.502 --> 05:05.072
[ Laughing ]

05:05.172 --> 05:07.074
Sir? You seem
pretty stable.

05:07.173 --> 05:09.742
Have you thought about
adopting one of our kids?
Sure haven't.

05:09.843 --> 05:13.413
Well, keep adoption in mind.
It's a great way to have a kid
without having sex.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.415
Really?

05:15.516 --> 05:19.353
Plus, the government
will help out with a small
stipend of $100 a week!

05:19.452 --> 05:22.689
A hundred dollars a week!
[ Gulping, Spitting ]

05:24.824 --> 05:27.326
I'm so sorry
I teased you back then.

05:27.427 --> 05:30.831
Let me make it up to you.
I can fix it so no one ever
makes fun of you again.

05:30.930 --> 05:32.832
You mean, by beating them up?

05:32.932 --> 05:36.504
Because I've broken that blind
kid's nose, like, ten times, and
it doesn't make any difference.

05:36.603 --> 05:39.606
No, I specialize
in phaser eye surgery.

05:39.706 --> 05:43.511
I can build you a paraffin
eye and graft it on
with skin from your foot.

05:43.610 --> 05:46.879
It won't be able to see,
but you'll look like
a perfectly normal...

05:46.980 --> 05:49.216
two-eyed person.

05:49.316 --> 05:52.620
Me? Perfectly normal?

05:55.187 --> 05:57.625
Hmm.

05:57.725 --> 06:00.226
Hmm!
[ Children Cheering ]

06:00.326 --> 06:02.529
Sons, daughters,
meet Uncle Fry.

06:02.629 --> 06:05.632
Hey, why are those kids
following you? Do you have
candy stuck to your ass?

06:05.733 --> 06:08.468
No, it's called "parenting."

06:08.569 --> 06:12.540
Come on, dumplings.
We've got 12 government
stipends to collect!

06:12.639 --> 06:15.408
Yea!
Our daddy's a giant toy!

06:17.076 --> 06:19.646
Phaser eye surgery
is a capital idea.

06:19.747 --> 06:24.216
I'm sure Leela's
tired of morons gaping
at her eye all the time.

06:25.317 --> 06:27.254
Oh-h-h!

06:27.353 --> 06:29.790
I think cosmetic surgery's
great, Leela.

06:29.889 --> 06:33.259
I used to be too cute,
so I had cuteness
reduction surgery.

06:33.360 --> 06:35.463
Here and here.

06:35.562 --> 06:38.566
You guys are crazy.
Leela doesn't need surgery.

06:38.665 --> 06:42.836
You look great
the way you are.
Oh, that's so sweet, Fry.

06:42.935 --> 06:45.404
But for once in my life,
I just want to look normal.

06:45.505 --> 06:48.108
But you're
better than normal.
You're abnormal.

06:48.207 --> 06:50.444
If you ask me, you shouldn't
care what other people think.

06:50.543 --> 06:53.613
You're right! I'll start by
not caring what you think.

06:53.713 --> 06:55.615
I'm getting the surgery!

06:55.716 --> 06:57.685
That-a-girl!
Right on!
Good call.

06:57.784 --> 07:00.319
Wonderful. And while you're
under the knife,

07:00.420 --> 07:03.322
you could also get
an ink pouch to help you
escape your enemies.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.660
That's the stupidest
idea I've ever heard,
you imbecile!

07:07.995 --> 07:10.798
Woo-woo-woo-woo-woo--

07:15.134 --> 07:17.771
Now, we'll find out
if the operation
was a success!

07:17.870 --> 07:20.507
Hold onto your hats.

07:29.216 --> 07:31.519
- [ Shocked Gasping ]
- Oh! I'm sorry.

07:31.619 --> 07:34.687
This is the wrong patient.

07:48.569 --> 07:50.036
[ Gasping ]

07:54.240 --> 07:57.177
Whoops!

07:57.276 --> 07:59.211
[ Squeaking ]

08:04.250 --> 08:06.853
Leela, those eyes
look so great on you.

08:06.954 --> 08:08.922
Bah! I think she looked
fine before.

08:09.021 --> 08:10.824
[ All Disagreeing ]

08:10.923 --> 08:13.593
Wow! Look at me!

08:13.694 --> 08:16.062
Although I don't have
the hang of blinking yet.

08:16.163 --> 08:20.167
You'll get it. Personally,
I try not to blink too much,
because it seems flashy.

08:20.266 --> 08:22.569
But when I do, I enjoy it.

08:23.670 --> 08:25.906
[ Gasping ]
Oh! I did it!
I blunk!

08:26.005 --> 08:28.841
And just in time
to screw up
this picture I took.

08:28.942 --> 08:33.446
- Hooray!
- ** [ "Pretty Woman" ]

08:44.390 --> 08:47.527
* Pretty woman
Walkin' down the street *

08:47.628 --> 08:50.597
- * Pretty woman
- [ All ] Ow! Ow! Ow!

08:50.697 --> 08:54.567
* The kind I like to meet
Pretty woman *

08:54.668 --> 08:58.238
* I don't believe you
You're not the truth *

08:58.337 --> 09:02.142
* No one could look
as good as you *

09:03.976 --> 09:06.980
* Mercy

09:08.649 --> 09:11.150
* Oh, oh
Oh!

09:11.250 --> 09:15.221
- * Pretty woman
- I've never felt
so unremarkable!

09:15.322 --> 09:19.426
Today, I actually
blended in with a crowd!
[ Laughs ]

09:21.961 --> 09:24.397
[ Giggling, Chattering ]

09:25.432 --> 09:27.835
Kids, meet the jerkbags
I work with.

09:27.934 --> 09:29.836
[ Together ]
Hello, jerkbags!

09:29.937 --> 09:33.005
Oh! They're so cute!
What are their names?

09:33.105 --> 09:37.309
- Kids have names?
- My name is Nina,
and his name's Albert--

09:37.409 --> 09:39.647
And from now on,
you're all named
Bender Junior!

09:40.813 --> 09:43.650
Looky here. My first
government stipend check.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.153
Twelve baby humans,
1,200 wing-wangs.

09:48.254 --> 09:51.692
Daddy Bender,
we're hungry!

09:51.792 --> 09:56.163
What is it with you kids?
Every other day,
it's food, food, food!

09:57.998 --> 10:01.500
Oh, fine. I'll get you
some stupid food.

10:01.600 --> 10:03.370
Could we have
Bender Burgers again?

10:03.470 --> 10:05.471
No! The cat shelter's
on to me.

10:09.341 --> 10:13.947
Hello, Leela. I was at
a nearby tailor, getting one of
my Hawaiian shirts toned down,

10:14.047 --> 10:16.115
so I thought I'd drop in
for your follow-up exam.

10:16.216 --> 10:18.518
[ Chuckling ]
Oh! That's so
handsome of you.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.821
Just follow the light
with your eyes.

10:23.355 --> 10:27.326
Perfect! You know, a guy
could fall head over heels
for a gal like you.

10:27.427 --> 10:29.562
As for me, I'm somewhat
interested myself.

10:29.663 --> 10:32.532
- What are you saying?
- I've never been good
with words--

10:32.631 --> 10:35.501
which is why I'm in
such a delicate conundrum.

10:35.601 --> 10:37.570
- Will you go out with me
this Sunday?
- Sure!

10:37.671 --> 10:41.240
- [ Gasps ]
- I don't know what else
to say, so I'll just say it.

10:41.341 --> 10:44.476
Okeydokey, see you then.

10:44.576 --> 10:47.980
This is so unfair.
I liked you back
when you were a cyclops.

10:48.081 --> 10:50.250
That guy's only interested
now that you have two eyes.

10:50.350 --> 10:52.985
- You're just jealous.
- No, I'm not!

10:53.086 --> 10:56.023
Oh, wait! I am!
But my point remains valid.

10:56.123 --> 10:59.091
Fry, I just want to try
dating a normal man,

10:59.192 --> 11:02.062
who, if you go
somewhere with him,
no one says he's crummy.

11:02.162 --> 11:04.831
I think I deserve that
once in life.

11:04.932 --> 11:08.836
Be careful with that
Adlai, Leela. He's a doctor.
They're very poor.

11:08.936 --> 11:11.370
Actually,
most doctors are rich.
What?

11:11.471 --> 11:15.207
When did this happen?
You're joking, right?
That's not funny!

11:17.443 --> 11:20.047
Okay, they got
everything you need here.

11:20.147 --> 11:22.048
Booze, a couple
of peanuts--

11:22.149 --> 11:25.518
They got a crapper in the back.
That's one of the things
you kids do, right?

11:25.618 --> 11:27.519
Yeah!
Then knock yourself out.

11:27.620 --> 11:29.355
[ Screaming, Laughing ]

11:29.456 --> 11:33.625
Hey! Hey! Only eat
and drink enough to barely
keep yourselves alive.

11:33.726 --> 11:36.263
I'm tryin' to make
a profit here.

11:39.599 --> 11:42.802
Daddy, Bethany's
hitting me!

11:42.903 --> 11:46.874
Here.
[ Laughing ]

11:46.974 --> 11:49.076
These kids yours?
Yeah.

11:49.176 --> 11:52.611
Ooh. I'm attracted to
a man with responsibility.

11:52.711 --> 11:55.783
That's me, baby.
Let me just ditch
the kids in an alley,

11:55.883 --> 11:58.585
and we can go
have some fun.
[ Knocking ]

11:58.684 --> 12:00.653
Daddy Bender?
Son?

12:00.754 --> 12:03.890
Daddy's tryin' to score
with a cheap floozy right now.

12:03.990 --> 12:06.658
So he needs you to cram
a Tinkertoy in it.

12:06.759 --> 12:09.395
I love you, Daddy Bender.

12:09.495 --> 12:11.498
[ Laughing ]
Hey! What the hell
are you doin'?

12:11.597 --> 12:14.134
Quit huggin' me.
I guess you're busy.

12:14.234 --> 12:18.071
- I'll catch you later.
- You morons! I don't know
what you're tryin' to pull,

12:18.171 --> 12:22.174
but I got half a mind to hug
each and every one of you
and see how you like it!

12:22.274 --> 12:27.080
[ All ] Yea!
Aw, come on!
[ Growling ]

12:29.950 --> 12:32.019
I thought I'd take you
someplace ordinary.

12:32.119 --> 12:35.322
A place no one
could object to.
That sounds wonderful.

12:42.328 --> 12:45.764
I'd like an
extra-beautiful bouquet, for
my extra-gorgeous sweetheart.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.770
Average, please.

12:53.340 --> 12:57.043
Oh, Adlai. I've had
a wonderful time today.

12:57.144 --> 13:00.179
No one's stared at me,
or avoided staring at me,

13:00.279 --> 13:02.182
or tried to burn me--

13:02.282 --> 13:04.817
You make me feel
so not weird.

13:04.918 --> 13:09.990
Leela, you're 999,999
in a million.

13:19.866 --> 13:23.336
[ Engine Whining,
Brakes Screeching ]

13:23.436 --> 13:25.672
Thanks for comin' out
to get to know my boyfriend.

13:25.772 --> 13:31.010
- Isn't he dreamy?
- Totally.
[ Munching Loudly ]

13:31.110 --> 13:36.216
Uh, listen. I just want you
all to know, your Leela's
one standard lady.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.551
Oh, Adlai!
Stop.

13:38.650 --> 13:41.187
What's so wonderful about
Leela being normal?

13:41.288 --> 13:44.224
The rest of us aren't normal,
and that's what makes us great.

13:44.323 --> 13:48.061
Like Dr. Zoidberg.
He's a weird monster who
smells like he eats garbage,

13:48.161 --> 13:50.029
and does.
Damn right!

13:50.129 --> 13:53.100
And the professor's
a senile, amoral crackpot.

13:53.200 --> 13:56.836
Oh, ay, eeh, ay.
Hermes is
a Rastafarian accountant.

13:56.937 --> 14:00.106
Tally me banana!
Amy's a klutz from Mars.

14:00.206 --> 14:03.676
- Oops!
- And Fry, you've got
that brain thing!

14:03.775 --> 14:07.179
I already did. So, Leela,
do you want to be like us?

14:07.279 --> 14:12.251
Or do you want to be like Adlai,
with no severe mental or social
problems whatsoever?

14:12.351 --> 14:15.522
That's the dumbest question
I ever heard.

14:15.621 --> 14:17.957
- She's right!
- No doubt about it!
- Daylight come.

14:19.025 --> 14:21.260
Comin' through.
Watch your head.

14:21.360 --> 14:24.797
- Help! I'm under attack!
- [ Disgusted Shouts ]

14:24.898 --> 14:29.701
Remember your manners, kids.
Forks go in the left pocket,
spoons in the right.

14:29.802 --> 14:34.106
Which one of you
cutie muffins gets
the children's spicy squab?

14:34.206 --> 14:36.209
Me!
Ap-dap-dap-dap!

14:36.308 --> 14:38.644
What do we say
when someone gives
you something?

14:38.745 --> 14:41.313
'Bout time!
That's my boy!

14:42.315 --> 14:44.484
And here's your check.
Bam!

14:44.584 --> 14:47.486
[ Shocked Gasp ]
I gotta go poopy.

14:47.586 --> 14:50.389
Well, you shoulda gone poopy
before it was time
to rat out on the check!

14:50.490 --> 14:52.392
Come on! Go! Go!
Through the kitchen!

14:52.491 --> 14:55.327
You little crooks!
If I catch you,

14:55.427 --> 14:57.830
I'm gonna make
cutie muffin gumbo!

14:57.931 --> 15:00.067
[ Bender Laughing
Wickedly ]
You know,

15:00.167 --> 15:02.802
seeing that strange robot
force 12 children
to do his bidding...

15:02.902 --> 15:04.836
makes me think about
kids of our own.

15:04.937 --> 15:08.441
Us? Me? You?
Kids?

15:08.541 --> 15:12.078
That's correct.
It's time to stop living
this vida bachelor loca.

15:12.178 --> 15:14.981
- Settle down and have kids.
- Oh, Adlai.

15:15.081 --> 15:18.184
This is the most beautiful
moment of my life.

15:18.284 --> 15:20.352
[ Zoidberg ]
Woo-woo-woo-
woo-woo-woo!

15:24.323 --> 15:26.625
[ All Screaming ]

15:28.195 --> 15:30.429
Daddy Bender, I want
a piggyback ride!

15:30.529 --> 15:33.633
Daddy's tired. Let's just
have another dog pile on Fry.

15:35.168 --> 15:38.270
[ Fry Groaning,
Children Laughing ]

15:38.370 --> 15:40.974
Tell us a story,
Daddy Bender!

15:41.073 --> 15:43.842
[ All Children ]
Story, story, story!

15:43.942 --> 15:47.313
All right, fine.
Gather around.
[ All ] Yea!

15:48.447 --> 15:50.817
We wanna hear
this one again.

15:52.184 --> 15:55.154
[ Clearing Throat ]
"Bender's Arrest Record.

15:55.254 --> 15:57.190
"By the Police.

15:57.289 --> 15:59.558
"On March 3, at 2:00 p.m.,

15:59.658 --> 16:01.660
Bender was caught
shoplifting."

16:01.760 --> 16:04.663
Yeah. Show us
the picture.

16:04.764 --> 16:07.500
[ Hysterical Laughing ]
[ Boy ]
Oh, there he is.

16:07.600 --> 16:10.503
Okay, kids.
It's 9:00, and you know
what that means.

16:10.602 --> 16:13.206
Daddy's sick o' lookin' at ya.
So go to bed.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.174
[ All ]
Aww!

16:15.274 --> 16:17.677
The grown-ups have to talk.
Come on, Ma.

16:20.013 --> 16:22.514
[ Light Switch Clicks ]

16:22.615 --> 16:26.552
Now, to figure out
how much money I'm rakin' in
off those twerps. [ Chuckles ]

16:29.155 --> 16:31.691
[ Muttering ]

16:31.791 --> 16:34.094
Ow!
I need a calculator.

16:34.193 --> 16:37.764
You a a calculator.
I mean,
a good calculator.

16:37.864 --> 16:40.832
Minus the food,
the bunny rabbit wallpaper--

16:40.932 --> 16:43.370
[ Shocked Gasp ]
I'm gettin' a hundred
bucks a kid,

16:43.470 --> 16:47.506
- and they're costin' me 110!
- Ugh. There goes my new
kitchen cabinets.

16:47.606 --> 16:50.110
I'm not sittin' through
one more P.T.A. meeting!

16:50.210 --> 16:52.445
The kids have
got to go.

16:52.544 --> 16:54.681
Daddy?
How do I flush you?

16:54.780 --> 16:56.849
[ Stammering ]
Just go to bed!

17:00.287 --> 17:03.090
[ Flushing Sound ]

17:09.528 --> 17:13.400
You know, doing
this jigsaw puzzle of
a pacifier factory...

17:13.500 --> 17:15.968
makes me
want to have children
with you all the more.

17:16.068 --> 17:17.936
Adlai, I was thinking.

17:18.037 --> 17:21.374
Since we're both orphans,
maybe we should adopt a child.

17:21.473 --> 17:24.277
Adoption?
Yes, that's acceptable.

17:24.376 --> 17:28.615
Heck, it's more
than acceptable, it's
adequately satisfactory.

17:33.220 --> 17:35.988
Hello? Imperial Dragon
Restaurant?

17:36.088 --> 17:38.657
I've got a herd of
you-know-whats for sale.

17:38.758 --> 17:40.826
Let me check.

17:40.926 --> 17:43.829
Oh, aren't you a cutie?

17:43.930 --> 17:45.932
About 35 pounds.

17:46.031 --> 17:48.134
[ Tapping Metal ]
What?

17:48.234 --> 17:52.471
- [ Yells Gibberish ]
- Hi, Bender. We'd like
to adopt a child.

17:52.572 --> 17:54.641
Well, you've come
to the right place.

17:54.740 --> 17:58.611
Because
Honest Bender's Orphanarium
means discount orphans.

17:58.711 --> 18:02.914
Now, little lady, what do I
have to do to send you home
with 12 orphans today?

18:03.015 --> 18:05.785
Uh, I'm afraid
we only want one.
Whatever you say, chief.

18:05.884 --> 18:07.787
I'll show you
what I got in stock.

18:07.886 --> 18:10.088
I remember this
from when we were kids.

18:10.190 --> 18:12.825
The warden would trot you out
in front of prospective parents,

18:12.924 --> 18:14.826
and they'd judge you
like a piece of meat.

18:14.926 --> 18:17.497
- I'm Albert.
- Kind of fatty.

18:17.596 --> 18:20.166
Then how 'bout
this little number?
Purebred human.

18:20.267 --> 18:24.971
- No vampire in there.
- Uh-- Mm--
- Hmm. Well, uh--

18:25.070 --> 18:28.807
If you're strapped for cash,
you might want to consider
this irregular unit.

18:28.907 --> 18:32.179
Cursed with a third ear,
but so full of that emotion...

18:32.278 --> 18:34.846
I understand
is called "love."

18:34.947 --> 18:38.116
One time, I did
a hundred jump ropes.

18:38.218 --> 18:41.887
Oh! I can't decide!
We're gonna have to
think about it.

18:41.988 --> 18:44.824
Okay, kids.
Grown-ups gotta talk now.
Time for bed.

18:44.923 --> 18:48.394
- But it's 10:00 in the morning!
- I said, hit the hay!

18:48.494 --> 18:51.330
[ Screaming, Laughing ]

18:53.500 --> 18:56.536
[ Clicks ]
[ Leela ] Oh, they're
all so adorable!

18:56.635 --> 18:58.837
Yeah. You know,

18:58.938 --> 19:02.509
it's times like this,
I can hardly bear
to let them go.

19:02.608 --> 19:05.377
Good night,
you princes of Maine!

19:05.478 --> 19:07.846
You kings
of New New England!

19:07.946 --> 19:09.981
You're under arrest
for child cruelty,

19:10.082 --> 19:12.519
child endangerment,
depriving children of food,

19:12.618 --> 19:15.755
selling children as food
and misrepresenting
the weight of livestock.

19:15.855 --> 19:19.526
- [ Electrical Buzzing ]
- If you had kids of your own,
you'd understand!

19:20.393 --> 19:22.161
[ Buzzer Sounding ]

19:22.261 --> 19:25.397
Officer, would it be
all right if we adopted
one of the kids?

19:25.498 --> 19:28.000
Might as well.
They're just gonna rot
in the evidence locker.

19:29.935 --> 19:33.005
Nice ear!
Ha, ha, ha!

19:33.105 --> 19:36.008
- Hey, Three Ears!
- [ All Taunting ]

19:36.107 --> 19:38.911
I've made up my mind.
Let's adopt her.

19:39.010 --> 19:41.280
Her? But there's
plenty of normal ones.

19:41.381 --> 19:44.517
Come on, Adlai.
She could really use
a mom and dad.

19:44.616 --> 19:49.288
[ Children ]
Ear Face! Ear Face!
Sally won the ugly race!

19:49.388 --> 19:51.758
On the other hand,
the children bring up
a good point.

19:51.857 --> 19:54.861
She does have
an ear on her face.
Well? So what?

19:54.961 --> 19:58.130
She may be different,
but she still deserves
a good home.

19:58.230 --> 20:01.067
Oh, all right. If you
really want that one,

20:01.166 --> 20:03.068
I can give her an operation
to make her acceptable.

20:03.169 --> 20:07.073
She doesn't need an operation!
She's fine the way she is.

20:07.173 --> 20:09.476
Oh, and I suppose
you were fine
the way you were?

20:09.576 --> 20:11.978
- Damn right I was!
- Yea!

20:12.077 --> 20:14.547
Shut up, Fry.
Now, look, Adlai.

20:14.646 --> 20:19.151
I'm proud to be different.
And I just wish I'd realized
that when I was her age.

20:19.251 --> 20:21.488
I also have a tail!

20:21.587 --> 20:25.325
Now, take me to the hospital
and put my eye back
the way it was. Right now!

20:25.424 --> 20:27.826
Why should I do that?
Listen, buddy.

20:27.926 --> 20:31.230
By the end of the day,
one of us is gonna
have one eye!

20:33.164 --> 20:35.934
In recognition of
Bender's generous gift...

20:36.035 --> 20:40.006
of 12 orphans and a government
check for 1,200 wing-wangs,

20:40.105 --> 20:43.075
I hereby rename
this building...

20:43.174 --> 20:46.313
the Bender B. Rodriguez
Orphanarium.

20:50.750 --> 20:53.586
It's good to have
the old, weird-looking
Leela back.

20:53.685 --> 20:56.188
Aw, you're
a true friend, Fry.

20:56.288 --> 20:58.857
I guess there's nothing wrong
with being a little weird.

20:58.958 --> 21:02.295
Leela, there's nothing
wrong with anything.

21:02.394 --> 21:07.299
We'll miss you, Daddy Bender.
We know robots don't
have emotions, but...

21:07.400 --> 21:09.602
we drawed you
this picture.

21:09.701 --> 21:13.472
So if you ever miss us,
even just a teeny bit,

21:13.573 --> 21:18.345
you can look at it.
Hey, I smoke a cigar,
not a candy cane. Sheesh!

21:21.647 --> 21:24.282
[ Disappointed Groaning ]

21:37.329 --> 21:39.665
[ Sighs ]

21:39.766 --> 21:41.667
[ Children ]
Yea!
Hey, what the-- Whoa!

21:41.768 --> 21:43.702
Get away! Come on.

21:43.802 --> 21:46.005
I just got all
the gum off of there.

21:46.105 --> 21:49.642
Hey! Hey!
[ Stammering ]
I hate you!

21:49.741 --> 21:51.844
I hate you all!
